{{zh-forms|[[桃园三结义]]|[[桃]][[園]][[三]][[結義]]}}
==Mandarin==
===Etymology===
From the ''[[w:Romance of the Three Kingdoms|Romance of the Three Kingdoms]]''
*Literally: the pledge of the three ([[w:Zhang Fei|Zhang Fei]], [[w:Guan Yu|Guan Yu]], and [[w:Liu Bei|Liu Bei]]) in the peach garden
[[Image:Three_Brothers.jpg|thumb|''Three Heroes of Three Kingdoms'', silk painting by Sekkan Sakurai (1715-1790). This painting is usually hung in the offices of businessmen to show that they were trustworthy, as these brothers were to each other.]]
===Idiom===
{{PAGENAME}} (''[[Pinyin]]'' táo yuán sān jiéyì, tao2yuan2san1jie2yi4)
# to become sworn brothers
# to join forces
#: ''[[備戰]]2008[[年]][[北京]][[奧運會]] [[中]][[日]][[韓]][[棒球]][[隊]]“'''桃園三結義'''”''[http://72.14.235.104/search?q=cache:AqPQXDFnNA0J:www.china.org.cn/chinese/zhuanti/2008ay/820386.htm+%E5%9B%BD%E9%99%85+%22%E6%A1%83%E5%9B%AD%E4%B8%89%E7%BB%93%E4%B9%89%22+site:.cn&hl=zh-CN&gl=cn&ct=clnk&cd=4]
#: ''The baseball teams of China, Japan and Korea '''join forces''' in preparation for the 2008 Olymipics in Beijing''

